_error_free.description: Internal function. Free the memory associated with `error`.

_transformation_free.description: Internal function. Free the memory associated with `transformation`.

_measurement_free.description: Internal function. Free the memory associated with `measurement`.

transformation_check.description: Check the stability relation of the `transformation` at the given `d_in`, `d_out`.

args.name: transformation
args.description: Transformation to check the stability relation of.

args.name: d_in
args.description: Distance in terms of the input metric.

args.name: d_out
args.description: Distance in terms of the output metric.

ret.description: True indicates that the relation passed at the given distance.

measurement_check.description: Check the privacy relation of the `measurement` at the given `d_in`, `d_out`.

args.name: measurement
args.description: Measurement to check the privacy relation of.

args.name: d_in
args.description: Distance in terms of the input metric.

args.name: d_out
args.description: Distance in terms of the output measure.

ret.description: True indicates that the relation passed at the given distance.

measurement_invoke.description: Invoke the `measurement` with `arg`. Returns a differentially private release.

args.name: measurement
args.description: Measurement to invoke.

args.name: arg
args.description: Input data to supply to the measurement. A member of the measurement's input domain.

transformation_invoke.description:
Invoke the `transformation` with `arg`. 
The response is not differentially private as it has not been chained with a measurement.

args.name: transformation
args.description: Transformation to invoke.

args.name: arg
args.description: Input data to supply to the measurement. A member of the transformations's input domain.

ret.description: Non-differentially private answer to the query.

args.name: measurement
args.description: outer privatizer

args.name: transformation
args.description: inner query

make_basic_composition.description: Construct the DP composition (`measurement0`, `measurement1`). Returns a Measurement.
